Definition: marked by practical hardheaded intelligence
Example: a smart businessman; an astute tenant always reads the small print in a lease; he was too shrewd to go along with them on a road that could lead only to their overthrow
Synonyms: noun, cognition, astuteness, sharp, sharpness, shrewd, shrewdness, marked, by, practical, hardheaded, intelligence, a, smart, businessman, an, tenant, always, reads, the, small, print, in, lease, he, was, too, to, go, along, with, them, on, road, that, could, lead, only, their, overthrow
Category: adj.all
